MAX SUM SUBARRAY OF SIZE K [GEEKS FOR GEEKS]

class Solution {
  public:
    int maxSubarraySum(vector<int>& arr, int k) {
        // code here
        int n=arr.size();   
        int sum=0;
//to select two initial elements
        for (int i=0; i<k;i++){
            sum=sum+arr[i];}
        int MaxSum=sum;
// to select the next element(sliding window)
        for (int i=k; i<n;i++){
            sum=sum+arr[i]-arr[i-k];
            MaxSum=max(sum,MaxSum);
            
        }
        return MaxSum;
}};


This approach is called the Sliding Window Technique 
Instead of calculating the sum from scratch for every possible contiguous block (which would take O(n^2)times, 
This technique optimizes the process to (O(n)) time complexity:
Initial Window: The first for loop calculates the sum of the first k elements (arr[0] to arr[k-1]). This establishes your baseline window.Sliding the Window: The second for loop slides this window one step to the right at a time.



